    ns1:numberOfCredits 6.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """* The schedule is based on an a priori planning of the subject; it might be modified during the academic year, depending on the number of enrolled students.
* This course invests a significant time and effort in laboratory activities. Since these activities take place in research facilities, small lab groups will be set at the beginning of the semester. Depending on the number of students some lab activities will take place in morning sessions.

Communication with students
* Communication between students and lectures will be through e-mail and Moodle. Any question or concern about the module should be sent to the coordinator. The lecturers will answer as soon as possible.
* Tutorials will take place face-to-face if possible or through Zoom.

Sustainable development goals
This module can contribute to SD Goal 4: Ensure inclusive and equitable quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all, in particular to targets 4.3 Ensure equal access for all women and men to affordable and quality technical, vocational and tertiary education, including university and 4.4 Substantially increase the number of youth and adults who have relevant skills, including technical and vocational skills, for employment, decent jobs and entrepreneurship.
As the module deals with microfabrication techniques for TIC components, we will have the opportunity to highlight SD Goal 9: Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure and its targets 9.5.Enhance scientific research, upgrade the technological capabilities of industrial sectors in all countries, in particular developing countries, including encouraging innovation and substantially increasing the number of research and development workers per 1 million people and public and private research and development spending and 9.8 Significantly increase access to information and communications technology and strive to provide universal and affordable access to the Internet in least developed countries."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Junio"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Febrero"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Febrero-Junio"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "60 horas y 25 minutos"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """In the subject Microelectronic Technology the students will deal with technologies currently used in the microfabrication of integrated circuits. The concept of technology is introduced as a concatenation of technological processes. Each individual process is described together with concepts about integration by highlighting the importance of their interrelation to built a complete technology.
The main objective is students becoming familiar with processes involved in the microfabrication of ICs and the fabrication technologies used currently."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/francisco.jimenez%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/alberto.almendra%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/francisco.jimenez%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Tecnologia Microelectronica"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CE10> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE10" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para diseñar y fabricar circuitos integrados."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CE15> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE15" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para la integración de tecnologías y sistemas propios de la Ingeniería de Telecomunicación, con carácter generalista, y en contextos más amplios y multidisciplinares como por ejemplo en bioingeniería, conversión fotovoltaica, nanotecnología, telemedicina."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CG2> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG2" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan aplicar los conocimientos adquiridos y su capacidad de resolución de problemas en entornos nuevos o poco conocidos dentro de contextos más amplios (o multidisciplinares) relacionados con su área de estudio."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CG4> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG4" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan comunicar sus conclusiones ?y los conocimientos y razones últimas que las sustentan? a públicos especializados y no especializados de un modo claro y sin ambigüedades."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CG5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes posean las habilidades de aprendizaje que les permitan continuar estudiando de un modo que habrá de ser en gran medida autodirigido o autónomo."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CT1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para comprender los contenidos de clases magistrales, conferencias y seminarios en lengua inglesa."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CT3> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT3" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para adoptar soluciones creativas que satisfagan adecuadamente las diferentes necesidades planteadas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CT4> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT4" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para trabajar de forma efectiva como individuo, organizando y planificando su propio trabajo, de forma independiente o como miembro de un equipo."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/CT5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para gestionar la información, identificando las fuentes necesarias, los principales tipos de documentos técnicos y científicos, de una manera adecuada y eficiente."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/RA122> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA122" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocer a nivel básico los procesos tecnológicos que se usan en la fabricación de circuitos integrados"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/RA124> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA124" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocer el concepto de tecnología de fabricación microelectrónica y saber diseñar esquemáticamente una ruta de fabricación de CI"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000836/2025-26/RA125> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA125" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Conocer las aplicaciones de las tecnologías microelectrónicas a dispositivos electrónicos particulares como dispositivos pasivos de alta frecuencia, sensores, MEMS, etc."@es .

